     The Company intends to retain any future earnings for working capital needs
and to finance capital improvements and presently does not intend to pay cash
dividends on the Common Stock for the foreseeable future. In addition the terms
of the Company's senior debt place certain limitations on the Company's ability
to pay cash dividends.
 
