million, $1.8 million and $18.0 million, respectively.
 
     Federal tax returns have been examined by the Internal Revenue Service
("IRS") through 1987. The statute of limitations has expired for years through
1991; however, the IRS can review such years to adjust any NOL's incurred in
such years and carried forward to offset income in subsequent years. Management
believes it has adequately provided for all taxes on income.
 
